QUEST BUILDER REFERENCE
=======================

All quest state is tracked by /daemon/quest_d.c. There is no separate
quest object to inherit. A complete quest needs three things:

  1. A definition in quest_d.c
  2. An NPC that starts and completes the quest
  3. An objective trigger (item pickup, room entry, NPC interaction)


PART 1: ADD A DEFINITION TO quest_d.c
--------------------------------------
Inside define_quests() in /daemon/quest_d.c, add:

    __quests["my_quest_id"] = ([
        "name"           : "Display Name",
        "giver"          : "npc_name",
        "start_location" : "One-line hint shown to player under 'quests'.",
        "desc"           : "Full quest description shown on accept.",
        "objectives"     : ([ "obj_key" : 1 ]),
        "reward_xp"      : 500,
        "reward_credits" : 300,
        "reward_infamy"  : 0
    ]);

Optional fields:
    "secret"         : 1          -- hidden until started
    "repeatable"     : 1          -- can repeat after cooldown
    "cooldown_secs"  : 86400      -- seconds between repeats (with repeatable)
    "level_min"      : 15         -- minimum level to complete
    "reward_lives"   : 1          -- grants an extra life on complete

objectives: each key maps to a required count. For a single step, use 1.
For kill quests, set a higher count and call update_objective incrementally.


PART 2: NPC THAT STARTS AND COMPLETES
--------------------------------------
In catch_tell() (or a call_out from it), call:

    /* Start */
    QUEST_D->start_quest(player, "my_quest_id");

    /* Complete (after all objectives are met) */
    QUEST_D->complete_quest(player, "my_quest_id");

    /* Check state before acting */
    QUEST_D->is_quest_active(player, "my_quest_id")
    QUEST_D->is_quest_complete(player, "my_quest_id")
    QUEST_D->is_objective_complete(player, "my_quest_id", "obj_key")

See /domains/Praxis/monsters/general_vendor.c for the full pattern:
  - offer_lost_supplies(): starts quest via say response to "work/job/quest"
  - try_complete_supplies(): checks inventory for item, removes it, completes

Also give a mid-quest reminder message (distinct from the "done" message)
so players who ask again get a useful hint, not just "nothing for you."


PART 3: OBJECTIVE TRIGGER
--------------------------
Three patterns:

  A. Item pickup (supply_crate.c):
     Override move() on the item. After ::move() returns 0 (success),
     call QUEST_D->update_objective(environment(this_object()), id, key, 1).

  B. Room entry (old_highway.c):
     In init(), check is_quest_active, then call_out("trigger_fn", 1, player).
     In trigger_fn(), verify player is still here, then update_objective
     and complete_quest.

  C. NPC interaction (deserter.c):
     In catch_tell() or a call_out handler, call update_objective.
     The completing NPC (Griz) checks is_objective_complete before
     calling complete_quest.


WORKING EXAMPLE
---------------
Quest: lost_supplies
  Definition : quest_d.c define_quests()
  NPC        : /domains/Praxis/monsters/general_vendor.c (Marta)
  NPC room   : /domains/Praxis/areas/general_store.c
  Item       : /domains/Praxis/equipment/supply_crate.c
  Item room  : /domains/Praxis/areas/old_highway.c
  Pattern    : fetch-and-return
  Flow:
    say work -> Marta starts quest -> player goes north
    -> picks up crate (objective auto-updates) -> say supplies to Marta
    -> Marta checks inventory, removes crate, completes quest
    -> quest_d grants 500 XP + 300 credits, prints reward message


PLAYER COMMANDS
---------------
  quests                -- active quests and objective progress
  quests completed      -- finished quests
  quests all            -- all visible quests with status
  quests <id>           -- detail on a specific active quest


NOTES
-----
- Reward messages are printed by quest_d.complete_quest(). Do not
  duplicate them in the NPC.
- Use say_here() not write() in NPC handlers (everyone in room sees it).
- Warmboot is sufficient after editing NPC or item files.
- quest_d.c requires a full reboot (it is preloaded at startup).
  Add new quests to define_quests() only; do not call register_quest()
  at runtime from NPC files.
